# ${project_name}

A neuro-san multi-agent project.

## Setup

1. Create and activate a virtual environment:

```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
```

2. Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

3. Configure your environment:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env and add your API keys
```

## Running the Project

### Quick Start with NSFlow UI

Start the neuro-san server and NSFlow UI together:

```bash
python run.py
```

Then open http://localhost:4173 in your browser to view and interact with your agents.

### Run Options

```bash
python run.py                    # Start both server and NSFlow
python run.py --server-only      # Start only the neuro-san server
python run.py --client-only      # Start only NSFlow (connect to existing server)
```

### Using the CLI (Direct Mode)

Run an agent directly without starting a server:

```bash
python -m neuro_san.client.agent_cli --agent hello_world
```

### Using the Server Manually

Start the neuro-san server:

```bash
python -m neuro_san.service.main_loop.server_main_loop
```

Then connect with the CLI:

```bash
python -m neuro_san.client.agent_cli --http --agent hello_world
```

## Project Structure

```
${project_name}/
├── registries/           # Agent network definitions
│   ├── manifest.hocon    # Lists which agents to serve
│   ├── llm_config.hocon  # Shared LLM configuration
│   └── hello_world.hocon # Example agent
├── coded_tools/          # Custom Python tools
├── run.py                # Start server and NSFlow UI
├── .env.example          # Environment template
├── .env                  # Your API keys (not in git)
└── requirements.txt      # Python dependencies
```

## Creating New Agents

Use the neuro-san CLI to scaffold new agents:

```bash
neuro-san new agent my_agent
```

Then add it to your manifest.hocon:

```hocon
"my_agent.hocon": true
```

## Creating New Tools

Scaffold a new CodedTool:

```bash
neuro-san new tool my_tool
```

